1. Resistor:
Opposes current
Unit: Ohm (Ω)
Used to control current
2. Capacitor:
Stores electrical energy temporarily
Unit: Farad (F)
Used in filters, timing circuits
3. Inductor:
Stores energy in magnetic field
Unit: Henry (H)
Used in transformers, filters
4. Switch:
Opens or closes a circuit
5. Battery:
Provides electrical energy (DC supply)
6. LED:
Emits light when current flows
